<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Once you realize that you are a hybrid youll be much happier with your class. Some of the people posting on your boards dont seem to realize that and act like they should have the same pet/casting power as a pure casting class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This doesn't exactly fly. Several reasons.<br>
<br>
One, don't mix &quot;casting&quot; and &quot;pet&quot; power willy nilly.  It's possible for beastlords to have decent &quot;pet&quot; power and crappy &quot;casting&quot; power overall.  Now both are crappy.  Beastlords were advertised as a &quot;pet-dependent melee/hybrid,&quot; which never existed before, so we can't just go assuming that &quot;pets&quot; are only supposed to be halfway decent when used by casters.  Think a little outside the box, just to be fair.  Beastlords paid a hefty price for their pets -- and that is that their melee power got JACKED.<br>
<br>
Two, lots of hybrids match or exceed &quot;pure&quot; classes in some areas.  Rangers exceed warriors in pure *offensive* melee, exceed warriors in archery, exceed druids in tracking, and match druids in snaring.  Other hybrids can say similar things, whereas currently beastlords seem to have everyone from all sides clamoring for them not to do anything well -- and heck, even being a close third with respect to pet damage (and a distant third with respect to pet tanking) is objectionable to some people.  /shrug<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Please dont go invoking the holy name of the epic pet when trying to point out how weak your pets are. Its a lot stronger than a regular pet because of the fact of the epic is absolute torture for mages to get and most will probably never see one in their spellbook.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you don't go invoking the holy grail of the 50% slow, then we have a deal. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Seriously, though, 9 out of 10 beastlords agree with you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   I think part of the problem with Beastmasters is the fact they want to be dish out a fair amount of melee damage, AND want their pets to be monsters too!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Could be.  Could also be that part of the problem with magickions (I'm allowed to mangle YOUR class name, right? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) is that they don't actually pay attention to what *most* people are saying, and zoom in on the minority.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Well know what? Ain't gonna happen... You, as Shadowknights, use your pet as a dot - your pet isn't supposed to be tanking for you.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Which is why lots of us aren't asking for it to be able to tank for us.  We are perfectly fine with doing our own tanking, but we are tanking with gimped AC, gimped HPs, gimped melee damage AND gimped pet giving love taps to the mob, then we're both going to get killed.  If we can't *take* much damage, then we should be able to dish it out.  Mages have to be pretty familiar with that concept.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Suggestions of aa that would make your pet stronger ( when WE - as THE pet class - do not have such a thing ) are nothing short of laughable.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And this is why so many people think you guys are rude.  If your aaxp is broken, then Verant should fix it, and you should suggest ways for them to do so.  But saying that they should keep ours busted just because you don't like what yours does is pretty selfish.<br>
<br>
From what I've read, the vast majority of pet-based aaxp ideas from mages don't overlap with the ideas that beastlords are coming up with anyway, so it seems that there are ways to make everyone happy.  And the ones that do overlap somewhat aren't that bad....I've seen beastlords suggest aa that would enhance their pet buffs, as have mages.  But it's kind of hard to avoid that problem since both sides have a ton of pet based spells. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90287 target=_blank> Bengali Grimmspirit</a><BR> 60 Vah Shir Savage Lord<br>
