<br>
I really do believe you guys need upgrades however not to the point that you are stepping on our toes. From all the parses I have seen warders do around 38 to 45dps on experience mobs. With enchanter haste and your atk buffs and the weapons that are available to your class a lvl 60 bst should be able to output 40 to 50 dps with melee on experience mobs. Beastlords have access to the best ratio weapons in the game just like monks. I have a lvl 60 epic bard and he can do 45 to 50dps on experience mobs and they do not have double attack either. Beastlord epic is uber easy to get and has 40% haste. With a 40% haste item + SoS and your atk buffs 40 to 48dps in only melee is very possible on experience mobs. If my bard can do it I know that you guys can. At the worse a lvl 60 bst will be able to do 80 to 85dps on experience mobs while having the ability to slow them 50%.<br>
<br>
85dps on experience mobs is very good for a melee. Only two melee classes in the game can get higher then that on experience mobs. Even uber warriors are hard pressed to do 85dps on experience mobs. On raids just about all melee are doing crappy damage so you are not alone. When you factor in spells and pet procs a bst can hit 90 to 95dps with ease with uber bst being able to get even higher. If we talk about end game then most bst can get up to 4300hps self buffed and 1400+ac. Don't tell me it isn't possible because there are a few on my server with these stats. Wielding 17/19 and 17/20 weapons also has there benefits.<br>
<br>
Basically a class that at end game can slow 50% get up to 4k+ hps and hit 1400ac while having the block skill and wielding the best ratio weapons in the game should not have a pet any where near a mage. I am sorry but it isn't going to happen. You have to look at the entire game not just where you are. Verant is balancing mages based on what they can do with all the best gear on because there are mages with the best gear. You might not have 17/19 weapons but many bst will get those and having a pet with water pet damage is way out of balance.<br>
